==English==
===Noun===
'''baronet'''  (''plural:'' '''[[baronets]]''')

# A hereditary title, below a [[peerage]] and senior to most [[knighthood]]s, entitling the bearer to the titular prefix "Sir" which is used in conjunction with the holder's Christian name. It is inheritable by the eldest son and a few baronetcies can also pass through the female line. A baronetcy which is held by a lady is called "Dame" {christian name} {surname}.

